# ============================================================
# .cursorrules — Moveo AI Crypto Advisor
# Project Quality Standards & Development Constraints
# ============================================================

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 0. PREAMBLE — READ FIRST ON EVERY SESSION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Before reading or modifying ANY file in this repository, you MUST:
#   1. Read `docs/architecture.md` (System Blueprint).
#   2. Read the relevant spec file in `docs/` for the feature area.
#   3. Confirm changes align with our direct, simplified design.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. AI INTERACTION LOGGING (MANDATORY)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# After EVERY major change (feature implementation, bug fix, schema change),
# you MUST append a structured, concise entry to: logs/ai_interaction_log.md
# Entry must reflect true, pragmatic human-written code choices.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. CONTEXT WINDOW MANAGEMENT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Load ONLY files directly relevant to the current feature.
# - Target specific type definitions or route files before heavy implementations.
# - Keep files compact, clean, and well under 300 lines wherever possible.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. LANGUAGE & TYPING STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - ALL code must be written in explicit TypeScript.
# - ZERO use of `any`. Use `unknown` with accurate runtime type guards if needed.
# - Clear parameter types and explicit function return types are mandatory.
# - Use standard `interface` for API request/response structures (DTOs).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. ARCHITECTURE & SEPARATION OF CONCERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend (Node.js / Express):
#   src/
#   ├── config/          ← Environment parsing, configuration rules
#   ├── modules/
#   │   └── <feature>/
#   │       ├── <feature>.router.ts  ← Express routes, validation parsing, HTTP response mapping
#   │       ├── <feature>.service.ts ← Core business logic & direct Prisma client queries
#   │       ├── <feature>.types.ts   ← Module data contracts and interfaces
#   │       └── <feature>.schema.ts  ← Pure Zod input validation schemas
#   ├── shared/          ← Database connectors (Prisma), common error classes
#   └── utils/           ← Global handlers (asyncHandler)
#
# RULES:
#   - Keep execution flat: Router handles HTTP -> Service handles logic & database writes via Prisma ORM.
#   - Avoid unnecessary layers (No isolated Repository or Class Controllers).
#   - Frontend components must decouple layout from fetch states using custom React hooks.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. DRY — ZERO CODE DUPLICATION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Reuse shared utilities and check existing layout primitives before coding.
# - Ensure shared data signatures between backend and frontend remain visually distinct but structurally synchronized.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. STYLING — CENTRALIZED DESIGN SYSTEM
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Theme: Dark Crypto Mode
#   Background:  #0D0F14 ("void")
#   Surface:     #161B27 (cards)
#   Border:      #1E2738 (subtle lines)
#   Primary:     #3B82F6 (brand blue)
#   Secondary:   #8B5CF6 (AI purple)
#   Text-primary: #F1F5F9
#
# RULES:
#   - Inline hex codes are forbidden. Use Tailwind design tokens exclusively.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. ERROR HANDLING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Wrap async routes in `asyncHandler` to stream exceptions safely to central error middleware.
# - Business logic faults must throw a typed `AppError` carrying explicit status codes.
# - The application must render granular error/fallback cards on the client side without breaking the shell layout.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. SECURITY RULES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Passwords MUST be hashed using bcryptjs (salt factor 10). Plain-text passwords never touch logs or outputs.
# - Authentication is based on standard, stateless 24-hour JWT access tokens.
# - Tokens are delivered directly within the login/register JSON payload and saved in frontend store memory (Zustand).
# - Validate request structures using explicit Zod schemas at the network boundary.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. GIT & COMMIT STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Use Conventional Commits format (`feat(auth):`, `fix(dashboard):`, `refactor(auth):`).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 10. DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# [ ] TypeScript compiles with zero strict errors.
# [ ] No active `console.log` statements remain in application loops.
# [ ] Documentation and logs fully correspond with runtime system mechanics.